    h3 = Hist1D(randn(10^3) .+ 0.5, -2:0.3:2)

<div class="markdown"><p>To plot a single histogram, you can do any of the following:</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    fig = Figure()
    p1, ax1= plot(fig[1, 1],h1; label = "plot(h1)")
    p2, ax2 = stairs(fig[1, 2], h1, label = "stairs(h1)")
    p3, ax3 = hist(fig[2, 1], h1, label = "hist(h1)")
    p4, ax4 = errorbars(fig[2, 2], h1, color=:black, whiskerwidth=6, label = "errorbars(h1)")
    axislegend.([p1, p2, p3, p4])
    fig
end</code></pre>
<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>


<div class="markdown"><p>When you're studying a single histogram, it's hepful to have statbox (CERN ROOT enjoyer?)</p><p>We provide a <code>statbox!()</code> function to add such box:</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    f_s = stairs(h1)
    statbox!(f_s, h1)
    f_s
end</code></pre>
<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>


<div class="markdown"><p><code>statbox</code> also works for 2D histogram as one'd expect:</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    h2d = Hist2D((randn(10000), randn(10000)))
    p2d = plot(h2d)
    statbox!(p2d, h2d)
    p2d
end</code></pre>
<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>


<div class="markdown"><p>You can freely combine these by using the bang <code>!</code> version to plot things on top of each other, for example this is some plot you might see:</p></div>


<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>


<div class="markdown"><p>But it's also pretty common to have multiple background components (processes), in such case, we often want a stacked histogram with error bar representing the sum of each component added up correctly.</p><p>We also have a recipe for that:</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>with_theme(ATLASTHEME) do
    f, a, p = stackedhist([h2, h2, h1 ])
    labels = ["proc1", "blah", "third one"]
    elements = [PolyElement(polycolor = p.attributes.color[][i]) for i in 1:length(labels)]
    title = "Legend title"
    Legend(f[1,2], elements, labels, title)
    f
end</code></pre>
<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>


<div class="markdown"><p>Notice the <code>with_theme(ATLASTHEME)</code>, you can apply a bunch of appearance tweaks for the entire plot.</p></div>


<div class="markdown"><p>Finally, we have a recipe for ratio plot which is argubaly useful for the bottom pannel in many plots:</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>with_theme(ATLASTHEME) do
    f_ratio, a, p = stairs(h1; label="h1")
    errorbars!(a, h1)
    stairs!(a, h3; label="h3")
    errorbars!(a, h3)
    
    axislegend()
    ratioax = Axis(f_ratio[2, 1], aspect = 5.5, xlabel = "my x-axis", ylabel="h1 / h3")
    linkxaxes!(ratioax, a)
    hidexdecorations!(a)
    ratiohist!(ratioax, h1/h3; color=:black, errors=true)
    rowsize!(f_ratio.layout, 1, Aspect(1, 0.5))
    f_ratio
end</code></pre>
<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>


<div class="markdown"><h1>Shading/Hatching errorbar band</h1><p>Until: https://github.com/JuliaPlots/Makie.jl/issues/1385#issuecomment-1166367423 is fixed, we don't have access to <code>LinePattern</code> driven shading, so you'd have to be creative and use <a href="https://makie.juliaplots.org/dev/examples/plotting_functions/crossbar/">crossbar</a>:</p></div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    f_crossbar = stairs(h1)
    statbox!(f_crossbar, h1)
    crossbar!(
        h1; 
        show_midline=false, 
        color=(:black, 0.5), 
        gap=0, width=diff(binedges(h1))
    )
    f_crossbar
end</code></pre>
<img height="450" src="data:image/png;base64, " style="object-fit: contain;" width="600"/>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>let
    f, a, p = stackedhist([h1, h1 ]; error_color=(:black, 0.5))

    elements = [PolyElement(polycolor = p.attributes.color[][i]) for i in 1:length(labels)]

    Legend(f[1,2], elements, labels, title)
    f
end</code></pre>
